description: Unigold Inc., a junior natural resource company, focuses on exploring and developing gold projects in Canada and the Dominican Republic. The company also explores for copper, silver, and zinc deposits. It holds an 100% interest in the Neita property covering an area of 21,031 hectares in the Dominican Republic. The company was formerly known as Caribgold Resources Inc. and changed its name to Unigold Inc. in December 2002. Unigold Inc. was incorporated in 1990 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Joseph Andrew Hamilton B.Sc (Hons), C.F.A., MSc, P.Geo.
